back in to help kill off the skeletal Lucan.  I got faction hit messages for the death of the skeletal Lucan, and that one kill took me from Amiable to very KoS.<br><br>So it's a big hit all by itself.<br><br>Anyone who wants to maintain non-KoS status in W/E.FP *must* zone out for *both* the death of the live Lucan *and* the death of the undead Lucan.<br><br>On the other hand, people who say that the faction hits will make you &quot;permanently&quot; KoS are wrong too.  I used the Inert Potion quest in Erudin to recover from the aforementioned faction hit, and then I killed both forms of Lucan for my own Soulfire (taking both faction hits).  I then recovered my non-KoS status in Freeport via two evenings of working the Inert Potion quest (that's a *lot* of mouse-clicking), and I am now actually at &quot;Allied&quot; status with the Freeport Militia (and *also* with the Hall of Truth, the N.FP Paladins).<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umystarria001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mystarria001</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/9/02 10:49:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3278.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lucan Lich Faction Hit?</span><hr size=1> I'm sure this has been beat to death and I'm sorry for bringing it up yet again.<br><br>Is the inert potion quest still active and does a high elf paladin of tunare have enough faction to start it?<br><br>Thanks<br><br>Azralia Sylvaresta<br>53rd Cavelier<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><